result.execSummary:
The defendant James H. Kuhnke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 2:38 pm [Clerk SH]
Defendant James H. Kuhnke in court with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa. ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing Arguments by Counsel

On Count #1, the Court sentences Mr. Kuhnke to 3 and 1/2  years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 18 months, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 2 years, consecutive. This sentence is IMPOSED & STAYED and the Court places Mr. Kuhnke on probation for 3 years, concurrent, with conditions: 
--serve 8 months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-Release privileges; to commence forthwith (may transfer to Columbia County)
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--To undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as per Agent
--No possession or consumption of alcohol
--No presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program or combination of the two, per Agent
--Comply with ALL family court orders regarding child support
--Make all child support payments on time
--Make all payments on arrearages according to the Child Support Orders
--Within 5 days of sentencing (or, if confined, within 5 business days of release from custody) defendant shall report to the child support agency-Jefferson County Courthouse, 311 S. Center Ave. Room 219,  Jefferson WI-to complete a case management meeting)
--Advise Child Support office of any employment or address change within 48 hours of such a change
--Not leave the State of Wisconsin without Court approval
--To pay $66 subpoena fees
--To pay costs of $268
--To pay $250 DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
All payments toward child support and arrearages are to be paid through: WISCONSIN SUPPORT COLLECTION TRUST FUND, PO Box 74200 Milwaukee, WI 53274-0200, NOT through DOC

If revoked: 
Conditions of Probation become conditions of extended supervision
The Court finds that Mr. Kuhnke is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program (Boot Camp) and the Substance Abuse Program.

The Court gives 0 days credit for time already served.
